title: 'Champions Trophy in the house': Akhtar overjoyed with 'beauty'

description: Former cricketer Harbhajan Singh has expressed concerns over India's potential Test debutant Nitish Kumar Reddy's lack of experience, particularly in the challenging conditions of Perth. He questioned the decision, drawing comparisons to seasoned all-rounders like Hardik Pandya and Shardul Thakur, who were not included in the Test squad.
title: 'Where is Shardul?': Harbhajan questions all-rounder selection for BGT

description: Bitcoin reached a new record high of nearly $95,000, driven by the introduction of options trading for major bitcoin ETFs and anticipation of potential crypto-friendly policies from the incoming Trump administration.  The surge also boosted MicroStrategy's shares significantly, as investors closely watch developments in the cryptocurrency market.
title: Bitcoin rises above $95,000 for the first time

description: During a virtual interaction for a new education program, Karnataka's Education Minister, Madhu Bangarappa, became enraged when a student seemingly remarked on his limited Kannada proficiency.  Bangarappa demanded action against the student, sparking criticism from the BJP who accused him of being undemocratic and unable to handle criticism.
title: 'Doesn’t know Kannada': Karnataka education minister orders action against student

description: A software executive from Mumbai fell victim to a sophisticated cyber fraud scheme, losing Rs 6.29 crore. Posing as CBI officials, the scammers placed the victim under "digital arrest," coercing him into transferring funds to avoid imprisonment for alleged money laundering activities. The Pune Cyber police are currently investigating the incident.
title: IT firm exec duped of Rs 6.3cr in biggest online fraud in Pune so far

description: WhatsApp is making customer service and utility messages free for businesses starting November 1, 2024. This move aims to challenge SMS dominance in India's enterprise messaging market, currently valued at Rs 2,500 crore. Telecom operators are protesting, claiming this will cause significant revenue loss. In response, Google and Vodafone Idea are promoting RCS messaging as an alternative.
title: Airtel, Jio, Vi and Google's 'WhatsApp problem' may have just grown bigger
Lawrence's brother Anmol applies for asylum in US
Bangladesh interim govt in a fix over Awami League inclusion in polls
Biren Singh's vow to crack down on 'militants' fails to stem stir
Smear campaigns will hit ties further, India tells Canada

description: Former Australian cricketer Matthew Hayden believes Akash Deep is the ideal replacement for Mohammed Shami in the Indian squad for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Hayden praised Prasidh Krishna's recent performance but highlighted Akash Deep's suitability for the fast and bouncy pitches in Perth and Adelaide.
title: Hayden endorses this bowler as Shami's replacement for BGT
India slips on climate list but still a high performer

description: Gautam Adani, along with other executives, has been charged by US prosecutors for allegedly bribing Indian officials. The alleged scheme aimed to secure solar energy contracts worth billions of dollars.  The charges include conspiracy to obstruct justice by deleting evidence and misleading US authorities. The SEC has also filed a civil lawsuit.
title: US charges Gautam Adani with bribery, fraud

description: A Hyderabad health department employee at the Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel National Police Academy fell victim to a cyber scam, losing ₹1.17 lakh. The scammers, posing as representatives of a PM healthcare scheme, tricked him into downloading a malicious app and revealing bank details.
title: Gone in 7 minutes: Cyber crooks con national police academy staff
Cal HC asks WB cops to 'take over' mosque after 1 killed in clashes
J&K joblessness rate highest, Delhi lowest
Focus on de-escalation: Rajnath to Chinese minister

description: Exit polls were released after the Maharashtra and Jharkhand assembly elections. Most polls suggest NDA has an advantage in both states. In Maharashtra, six out of ten polls favor NDA. In Jharkhand, three out of seven polls give NDA a clear majority. Counting of votes will take place on November 23.
title: Exit polls give NDA edge in Maharashtra & Jharkhand, but will results match?

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi was awarded Dominica's highest honor, the "Dominica Award of Honour," for his support during the COVID-19 pandemic and his commitment to strengthening India-Dominica ties. The award was presented by Dominica's President, Sylvanie Burton, during the India-CARICOM Summit in Guyana.
title: PM Modi honoured with Dominica's top civilian award

description: A man arrested for a house burglary in Karwar turned out to be a seasoned thief with over 100 cases in Bengaluru and more in Goa and Punjab.  Sameer Sharma, operating solo, targeted homes during the day, scouting for unlocked windows and doors. His motive stemmed from a desire for greater income than his electronics shop provided.
title: A lone wolf, this daylight burglar faces 100 cases, 30 warrants & 20 notices
